WEBVTT

00:01.067 --> 00:02.334
<i>Previously on "Switched at Birth"... </i>

00:02.368 --> 00:04.269
You should clean this up if
you're gonna have company over.

00:04.304 --> 00:05.504
We should have gotten our stories straight.

00:05.538 --> 00:07.306
- Regina Vasquez?
- Yeah.

00:07.340 --> 00:09.341
Come with me, please. Unfortunately
these kinds of red flags

00:09.375 --> 00:12.478
require me to refer your case to
our fraud investigation department.

00:12.512 --> 00:15.447
- This is for you.
- It's a letter from Frida Kahlo to Diego.

00:15.482 --> 00:18.102
They don't even sell these.
Most of them are in museums.

00:18.103 --> 00:18.842
Are you sure it's real?

00:18.843 --> 00:21.129
_

00:21.130 --> 00:23.781
_

00:23.782 --> 00:25.288
_

00:25.291 --> 00:27.059
No turning back now.

00:27.093 --> 00:28.460
So that's how you wanna win this thing?

00:28.495 --> 00:30.462
By saying nothing of substance?

00:30.497 --> 00:34.399
I'm sorry, but I think Ivan is
right. No more talking politics.

00:35.502 --> 00:37.469
Then consider your wife reined in.

00:39.038 --> 00:41.106
- Thanks.
- No problem.

00:42.408 --> 00:44.309
- Girl or boy?
- A girl.

00:44.344 --> 00:47.179
Oh, exciting.

00:47.213 --> 00:49.014
So crazy me, I thought maybe

00:49.048 --> 00:51.950
you wanted to know that you
had another one on the way.

00:51.985 --> 00:53.018
You just gonna walk out on another kid?

00:53.052 --> 00:55.954
- This is not the same.
- It is to the kid.

00:55.989 --> 00:58.223
It is the same thing all over again.

01:01.094 --> 01:03.095
- Did he say anything to you?
- I don't know.

01:03.129 --> 01:05.230
- It must be a mistake.
- He didn't say anything?

01:05.265 --> 01:07.132
No, nothing.

01:10.169 --> 01:12.771
Hey, can I talk to you
guys about something?

01:12.805 --> 01:15.741
That's funny. We were about
to ask you the same question.

01:15.775 --> 01:17.743
What the hell is this?

01:17.777 --> 01:19.077
It's a credit card bill.

01:19.112 --> 01:20.746
That is correct...

01:20.780 --> 01:24.049
with a $400 prenatal ultrasound charge.

01:24.083 --> 01:25.984
Oh, yeah.

01:26.019 --> 01:27.719
Is there something you need to tell us?

01:27.754 --> 01:29.688
I thought Nikki was a good Christian girl.

01:29.722 --> 01:31.056
Not that Christian.

01:31.090 --> 01:33.025
It's not Nikki's.

01:33.059 --> 01:35.027
Oh, Toby.

01:35.061 --> 01:37.763
No no no no, I didn't get anybody pregnant.

01:37.797 --> 01:39.631
The ultrasound was for Lana.

01:39.666 --> 01:42.100
- Wait, how did you even...
- Angelo's Lana.

01:42.135 --> 01:44.670
I ran into her at the mechanic's,

01:44.704 --> 01:47.639
and I gave her a ride home and that's
when I got into that fender bender.

01:47.674 --> 01:49.575
So I took her to the E.R.
to make sure she was okay.

01:49.609 --> 01:51.743
Whoa, wait a sec. So I'm now paying

01:51.778 --> 01:54.646
for prenatal care for Angelo's floozy?

01:54.681 --> 01:55.981
Dad, she's not a floozy.

01:56.015 --> 01:59.585
Whatever you think about
Angelo, it's not her fault.

01:59.619 --> 02:01.520
<i>- It's half her fault.
- (Sighs)</i>

02:01.554 --> 02:03.722
Lana's family's in Boston. She's all alone.

02:03.756 --> 02:05.524
She seemed like she needed some help.

02:05.558 --> 02:07.426
What am I supposed to do?
Just look the other way?

02:07.460 --> 02:09.627
- Toby, this is Angelo's problem.
- (Scoffs)

02:09.662 --> 02:13.532
Honestly, I thought you guys would
be way more supportive about this.

02:13.646 --> 02:15.881
I really think you guys should meet her.

02:15.915 --> 02:17.582
Why?

02:17.617 --> 02:21.420
Because she's carrying Bay's sister.

02:21.454 --> 02:23.689
- Look, we appreciate you wanting to help...
- Good,

02:23.723 --> 02:25.590
because I invited her to dinner.

02:28.577 --> 02:34.580
- synced and corrected by chamallow -
- www.addic7ed.com -

02:34.600 --> 02:37.402
(Engine idles, stops)

02:39.539 --> 02:42.374
<i>Angelo: Bay, I'm glad you're here.</i>

02:43.810 --> 02:47.779
Bay, wait. Can we please talk about this?

02:47.814 --> 02:50.449
- We did and you lied.
- I know. I'm sorry.

02:50.483 --> 02:52.484
Wow, you should just
get that on a t-shirt.

02:52.518 --> 02:53.819
- It would really move things along.
- Bay.

02:53.853 --> 02:56.888
Why is Angelo's settlement
money parked in my driveway?

02:56.923 --> 02:59.825
I don't know. I think he's trying
to patch things up with Bay.

02:59.859 --> 03:02.327
Huh.

03:02.361 --> 03:05.530
Ooh, doesn't look like it's
going very well for Angelo.

03:05.565 --> 03:09.434
Oh, I wish Daphne were here.
She could read their lips.

03:09.469 --> 03:11.636
<i>- Kathryn: There goes a finger in the face.
- Oh, boy.</i>

03:11.671 --> 03:14.339
He strikes out!

03:14.373 --> 03:17.709
(Sighs) It's nice not to be at
the receiving end of one of those.

03:17.744 --> 03:20.445
So if Bay is done with Angelo,

03:20.480 --> 03:21.747
can we be, too?

