05:43.990 --> 05:47.859
Travis's parents are kicking him out.

05:47.894 --> 05:51.830
And I think that we should
talk to John and Kathryn, but...

05:51.864 --> 05:54.900
But Travis doesn't want you to.

05:54.934 --> 05:57.002
Been down that road.

05:57.036 --> 06:00.639
But you know him better than I do.

06:00.673 --> 06:03.575
Is this like a "don't tell your dad,

06:03.609 --> 06:05.710
but secretly I want you

06:05.745 --> 06:07.812
to tell your dad"?

06:07.847 --> 06:10.515
Or is it just a "don't tell your dad"?

06:10.549 --> 06:13.518
I don't know.

06:13.552 --> 06:16.554
But they'd let him stay here, right?

06:16.589 --> 06:19.591
Apparently, even those
carrying Angelo's spawn

06:19.625 --> 06:20.859
are welcome.

06:20.893 --> 06:23.662
Right, the dinner. I
feel bad you have to go.

06:23.696 --> 06:26.531
Bad enough to join me?

06:26.565 --> 06:28.466
No way.

06:29.735 --> 06:32.437
My baby back ribs always go fast.

06:32.471 --> 06:34.472
And I'll serve salad with dinner.

06:34.507 --> 06:36.474
That'll shave 20 minutes off the night.

06:36.509 --> 06:40.378
How come Daphne and Regina get to
boycott and we get stuck hosting?

06:40.413 --> 06:42.347
Just be grateful Angelo's not coming.

06:42.381 --> 06:46.284
He's the cause of all
this. He gets to skip, too?

06:46.319 --> 06:49.421
(Sighs) Toby says that
Lana is still not sure

06:49.455 --> 06:52.424
- how Angelo fits in.
- At least we have that in common.

06:52.458 --> 06:54.693
All right, I am off to the market.

06:54.727 --> 06:57.295
- What do you want for dinner tonight?
- That reminds me...

06:57.330 --> 06:58.630
set a place for Ivan. He's popping by later

06:58.664 --> 07:01.232
to discuss internal polling data.

07:01.267 --> 07:03.435
Oh, well, then I'll stay out of your way.

07:03.469 --> 07:06.237
You know where the
takeout menus are, right?

07:13.546 --> 07:16.114
- Excuse me.
- If you have a problem with the ticket,

07:16.148 --> 07:18.383
you have to take it up with the city.

07:18.417 --> 07:21.419
I'm Daphne. I go to school with Travis.

07:21.454 --> 07:24.222
Oh, right. The one that can talk.

07:24.256 --> 07:26.491
Yeah.

07:26.525 --> 07:30.462
- Did you know that he's been...
- What's he done this time?

07:30.496 --> 07:33.198
- Uh...
- What's he done?

07:33.232 --> 07:37.102
Nothing. I just want you to
know how great your son is.

07:37.136 --> 07:39.137
Oh, okay.

07:41.007 --> 07:44.242
You know, Carlton offers free A.S.L.
classes to parents on Thursday nights.

07:44.276 --> 07:47.912
Oh, right. I'm gonna fit
that in right after work...

07:47.947 --> 07:50.115
before I have to go take care of my mom,

07:50.149 --> 07:52.117
who can't even get out of bed.

07:52.151 --> 07:54.285
And then I'm gonna go home
and I'm gonna make dinner,

07:54.320 --> 07:56.221
clean up the house...

07:56.255 --> 07:58.823
none of which Travis helps me with.

07:58.858 --> 08:02.761
And you're kicking him
out of the house for that?

08:02.795 --> 08:04.896
Is that what he told you?

08:04.930 --> 08:07.098
It's not true?

08:07.133 --> 08:09.067
Did he tell you about the
fights he's been getting into

08:09.101 --> 08:11.803
with his brother and his dad?

08:13.172 --> 08:16.775
Yeah, I bet he didn't.

08:16.809 --> 08:19.677
He's the one that's
threatening to move out.

08:19.712 --> 08:22.647
And honestly... (Sighs)

08:22.681 --> 08:24.049
maybe it's just for the best.

08:28.120 --> 08:29.788
<i>(Knock on door)</i>

08:31.712 --> 08:33.679
I've been thinking about this.
And that woman is coming here.

08:33.714 --> 08:35.682
She is coming to this house.

08:35.716 --> 08:37.450
I know.

08:37.485 --> 08:40.419
Well, that's ridiculous. You're
gonna just let that happen?

08:40.453 --> 08:42.455
<i>- Not my house.
- He makes these messes,</i>

08:42.490 --> 08:44.491
and then he expects all
of us to clean it up.

08:44.525 --> 08:47.460
And I am so sorry that I got
you involved in any of this.

08:47.495 --> 08:50.597
Honey, I knew him years
before you were even born.

08:50.631 --> 08:52.299
You married him for me,

08:52.333 --> 08:54.467
and I feel so terrible about that.

08:54.502 --> 08:56.603
That is not your fault.

08:56.637 --> 08:59.139
I have no regrets.

08:59.173 --> 09:01.508
Okay, if I could get in a
time machine and go back,

09:01.542 --> 09:03.310
I probably wouldn't marry him again.

09:03.344 --> 09:06.346
- But I did...
- We should warn her.

09:06.380 --> 09:08.481
- Who?
- Lana.

09:08.516 --> 09:11.451
We should tell her what
she's getting into with him.

09:11.485 --> 09:14.187
I don't think you should get involved.

09:14.222 --> 09:15.455
I'm going to that dinner,

09:15.489 --> 09:19.125
and I'm going to tell her exactly
what kind of guy Angelo is.

09:24.874 --> 09:26.841
<i>- (Knock on door)
- Come in!</i>

09:28.844 --> 09:30.578
Smells good. What are you making?

09:30.613 --> 09:32.681
Old family recipe.

09:32.715 --> 09:34.783
Pop-tarts.

09:34.817 --> 09:37.819
If you're here to talk me into coming
to your party for Angelo's baby mama,

09:37.853 --> 09:39.421
the answer is "no."

09:39.455 --> 09:41.556
No, that's not why I'm here.

09:41.590 --> 09:43.425
But we're not happy about it, either.

09:43.459 --> 09:46.695
John and I only said yes to this dinner
'cause we figured that you'd kill it.

09:46.729 --> 09:49.631
- We need to work on our good cop/bad cop.
- (Chuckles)

09:49.665 --> 09:51.299
So what's up?

09:51.334 --> 09:55.270
I was wondering if maybe you
wanted to get out of here,

09:55.304 --> 09:56.705
go have some fun.

09:56.739 --> 10:00.375
Would this involve heels?

10:00.409 --> 10:02.277
Could.

10:10.453 --> 10:13.521
So you have a Frida Kahlo
letter and you want to sell it?

10:13.556 --> 10:16.624
If it's actually worth
anything. My dad gave it to me.

10:16.659 --> 10:19.160
I'm sure it's a fake.

10:19.195 --> 10:21.429
I have a bunch of mumbo jumbo

10:21.464 --> 10:23.231
from the auction house,

10:23.265 --> 10:26.234
and it probably means more
to you than it does to me.

10:29.338 --> 10:31.239
(Laughs)

10:31.273 --> 10:33.475
This was one of Frida's
unsent letters about Leonardo.

10:33.509 --> 10:36.544
- Uh, who's Leonardo?
- Her son.

10:36.579 --> 10:39.214
I thought that after the bus accident

10:39.248 --> 10:41.516
- she couldn't have any children.
- She couldn't,

10:41.550 --> 10:44.419
so she created an imaginary
son she called Leonardo.

10:44.453 --> 10:47.422
Really? I've never read anything.

10:47.456 --> 10:50.091
Oh, yeah. She made paintings
for him and wrote letters about

10:50.126 --> 10:52.961
- the life she wanted them to have together.
- That's so sad.

10:52.995 --> 10:55.263
She burned all the letters,

10:55.297 --> 10:57.198
but I guess somehow this one survived.

10:57.233 --> 11:01.002
Are you sure you want to part with this?

11:04.140 --> 11:06.107
- (Jazz music playing)
- (Chattering)

11:08.144 --> 11:10.879
Oh. I love this place.

11:10.913 --> 11:13.248
I used to come here all
the time with Angelo,

11:13.282 --> 11:15.049
way back in the day.

11:19.255 --> 11:21.823
- Hi, ladies.
- Hi.

11:21.857 --> 11:23.191
- Can I get you something to drink?
- Yes.

11:23.225 --> 11:25.160
- Club soda with lime, please.
- Sure.

11:25.194 --> 11:27.162
- Make that two.
- Okay.

11:27.196 --> 11:30.999
Oh, uh... Kathryn, I'm
fine. Order what you want.

11:31.033 --> 11:32.667
It is what I want.

11:33.803 --> 11:36.771
Okay, I'll take a pink panty-dropper.

11:36.806 --> 11:39.107
- All right.
- (Laughs)

11:39.141 --> 11:41.810
Vodka, beer, pink lemonade.

11:41.844 --> 11:43.077
- Oh. I'm guessing...
- (Chuckles)

11:43.112 --> 11:45.780
You needed to get out of
the house more than I did.

11:45.815 --> 11:47.715
Ugh! John's campaign.

11:47.750 --> 11:49.751
What? I thought you'd be a natural.

11:49.785 --> 11:52.921
Apparently not. I have "too many opinions."

11:52.955 --> 11:54.823
- Oh.
- I'm supposed to smile

11:54.857 --> 11:56.724
and be the happy homemaker.

11:56.759 --> 12:00.462
It should be easy. I've
had plenty of practice.

12:03.766 --> 12:05.667
Oh my God.

12:05.701 --> 12:09.637
- What?
- Zane.

12:09.672 --> 12:10.772
When I used to come here,

12:10.806 --> 12:13.675
he always used to hit
on me in front of Angelo.

12:13.709 --> 12:17.545
It was kind of nice to have
the shoe be on the other foot.

12:17.580 --> 12:19.380
<i>He's gorgeous.</i>

12:19.415 --> 12:22.383
He reminds me of a guy I dated in college.

12:22.418 --> 12:23.585
He was a musician?

12:23.619 --> 12:26.321
- No.
- Oh.

12:26.355 --> 12:29.691
- Why are you so surprised?
- Well, I guess...

12:29.725 --> 12:32.360
You're right. I shouldn't be.

12:32.394 --> 12:34.395
His name was Chester. He flew airplanes.

12:34.430 --> 12:36.731
One time he took me to D.C. for dinner

12:36.765 --> 12:38.633
- in a little five-seater.
- Oh.

12:38.667 --> 12:41.436
I've been in one of those. I was terrified.

12:41.470 --> 12:45.406
Not me. Mnh-mnh. Mnh-mnh.

12:45.441 --> 12:47.275
Um...

12:47.309 --> 12:50.512
how did your mom take you dating Chester?

12:52.314 --> 12:54.649
- I never told her.
- (Chuckles)

12:54.683 --> 12:57.185
You should go over there and talk to him.

12:57.219 --> 12:58.520
Oh, please. I doubt he even remembers me.

12:58.554 --> 13:00.488
Really?

13:02.157 --> 13:04.225
He's coming over here right now.

13:06.195 --> 13:08.363
<i>- Reggie?
- Regina: Hi.</i>

13:08.397 --> 13:11.132
- Is that you?
- Yeah, wow.

13:11.166 --> 13:12.534
What's it been, 15 years?

13:12.568 --> 13:15.470
Yeah, you don't look like it.

13:15.504 --> 13:19.140
Kathryn, this is Zane. Zane, Kathryn.

13:19.174 --> 13:21.309
- Kathryn, very nice to meet you.
- Hi, nice to meet you.

13:21.343 --> 13:24.212
So you and Angelo still together?

13:24.246 --> 13:26.347
No.

13:26.382 --> 13:28.349
Hmm.

13:30.185 --> 13:32.253
I think I'm gonna go powder my nose.

13:33.389 --> 13:34.989
Excuse me.

13:36.025 --> 13:38.293
- May I?
- Please.

13:40.396 --> 13:43.231
I thought I heard that
you moved to New York.

13:43.265 --> 13:47.201
Wait. Didn't I hear that
you played Lincoln Center?

13:47.236 --> 13:49.003
This is true.

13:49.038 --> 13:51.973
That's incredible. What
are you doing back here?

13:52.007 --> 13:54.976
Uh, I had my time in the big leagues,

13:55.010 --> 13:56.844
lost sight of the simple things.

13:56.879 --> 13:58.179
And plus, I like it here in Kansas City.

13:58.213 --> 14:01.049
My mom's here. My sister's here.

14:01.083 --> 14:02.750
(Laughs)

14:02.785 --> 14:05.153
I always used to talk
about moving to New York,

14:05.187 --> 14:09.023
and then I realized I'm
a small pond kind of gal.

14:09.058 --> 14:11.759
- I know what you mean.
- (Both chuckle)

14:13.796 --> 14:16.798
Unfortunately, I gotta be across town.

14:16.832 --> 14:18.866
You need to come back tomorrow night.

14:18.901 --> 14:21.903
Me and the guys are gonna be
playing. It's gonna be a great set.

14:21.971 --> 14:24.672
Maybe I will.

14:24.707 --> 14:26.741
Okay.

14:31.681 --> 14:33.349
<i>Announcer: Illegal
immigrants are taking our jobs</i>

14:33.383 --> 14:35.251
<i>and draining Kansas resources.</i>

14:35.285 --> 14:37.253
<i>Everyone knows it's a
problem except John Kennish.</i>

14:37.287 --> 14:39.154
<i>Just listen to what his wife says... </i>

14:39.189 --> 14:41.557
<i>Kathryn's voice: John believes
in giving everyone the opportunity</i>

14:41.591 --> 14:44.126
<i>to take their shot at the American dream.</i>

14:44.160 --> 14:47.363
Unlike John Kennish, I want to
make sure Americans have a shot

14:47.397 --> 14:49.098
at the American dream.

14:49.132 --> 14:51.166
<i>Man: John Kennish. Wrong on immigration.</i>

14:51.201 --> 14:52.301
<i>Wrong for Kansas.</i>

14:52.335 --> 14:53.535
I'm Patricia Sawyer,

14:53.570 --> 14:56.272
<i>- and I approve this message.
- Announcer: Paid for... </i>

14:56.306 --> 14:58.240
Okay, she can't run that.

14:58.275 --> 15:00.142
They already are.

15:00.176 --> 15:03.279
It's all over their website.
It'll be on TV by the weekend.

15:03.346 --> 15:05.214
I cannot believe she would stoop this low.

15:05.248 --> 15:08.017
This is why I didn't
want Kathryn giving them

15:08.051 --> 15:09.351
any ammunition with that interview.

15:09.386 --> 15:12.921
(Sighs) So what do we do now?

15:12.956 --> 15:15.924
Fortunately, we have a bigger bombshell
than some stray comment on immigration.

15:15.959 --> 15:17.893
Like what?

15:17.927 --> 15:20.129
Footage of her saying we
should legalize marijuana.

15:20.163 --> 15:22.898
What, she actually said that?

15:22.932 --> 15:25.067
When she was on her college debate team.

15:25.101 --> 15:26.802
You don't think she really believes that.

15:26.836 --> 15:28.137
It doesn't matter what I believe.

15:28.171 --> 15:31.840
We show people that you're a patriot.

15:31.875 --> 15:33.042
And we'll show Sawyer

15:33.076 --> 15:36.078
as some soft-on-crime pothead.

15:36.112 --> 15:38.747
Voters'll make up their own mind.

15:47.157 --> 15:51.026
So what crappy thing happened to you today?

15:51.061 --> 15:52.928
What?

15:52.962 --> 15:55.798
You're shooting baskets at night.

15:55.832 --> 15:58.600
It's kind of your go-to when you're upset.

16:00.870 --> 16:03.539
I went to see Travis' mom today.

16:03.573 --> 16:05.941
She said they're not throwing him out.

16:05.975 --> 16:08.744
Is that not good news?

16:08.778 --> 16:11.947
She said he's the one who
doesn't want to be there.

16:11.981 --> 16:15.484
I mean, I'm sure it's not
the happiest place on earth,

16:15.518 --> 16:18.554
but it's better than being homeless.

16:18.588 --> 16:21.790
Hmm. If only there was a place

16:21.825 --> 16:24.860
with lots of empty rooms

16:24.894 --> 16:27.730
that wouldn't charge him rent.

16:27.764 --> 16:31.533
I tried, but for whatever
reason, he won't let me help him.

16:31.568 --> 16:34.403
(Scoffs) Because he likes you.

16:35.538 --> 16:37.673
I know.

16:37.707 --> 16:40.376
All right, I'm just gonna ask.

16:40.410 --> 16:41.777
Do you like him?

16:41.811 --> 16:43.746
No.

16:43.780 --> 16:47.583
Really? You're not into deaf Matt Damon?

16:47.617 --> 16:49.318
Not even a little bit?

16:49.352 --> 16:50.586
No.

16:53.390 --> 16:55.357
Good.

16:55.392 --> 16:58.627
Because I've been hooking up
with him for the last month.

16:58.661 --> 17:00.462
What? You have?

17:00.497 --> 17:02.264
No.

17:02.298 --> 17:04.366
I just wanted to see

17:04.401 --> 17:07.102
if you had a jealous reaction,

17:07.137 --> 17:09.371
which you kind of did.

17:09.406 --> 17:13.075
Maybe you're more into him

17:13.108 --> 17:14.510
than you think.

17:21.217 --> 17:23.484
I'm sorry they're using
my interview against you,

17:23.520 --> 17:25.988
but this... this isn't right.

17:26.021 --> 17:27.321
I didn't make her say it.

17:27.357 --> 17:30.325
It was a college debate, John.

17:30.360 --> 17:33.162
She didn't get to choose
what side she argued.

17:33.196 --> 17:36.131
Besides, you supported all kinds of
crazy things when you were that age.

17:36.166 --> 17:38.033
I didn't do it on tape.

17:39.302 --> 17:42.004
Don't let Ivan drag you into the gutter.

17:42.038 --> 17:44.072
If you don't fight back,
they think you're weak,

17:44.107 --> 17:46.308
and they hit you even harder.

17:46.342 --> 17:48.877
Okay, do what you want, John.

17:48.912 --> 17:51.146
'Cause that's what you're gonna do anyway.

18:00.722 --> 18:02.623
We're here!

18:02.657 --> 18:05.525
<i>- Kathryn: Oh, hi.
- John: Hello.</i>

18:05.560 --> 18:07.427
John Kennish. How are you?

18:07.462 --> 18:11.632
- Um, pregnant. How are you?
- (Laughing)

18:11.666 --> 18:14.234
Kathryn Kennish. You look fantastic.

18:14.269 --> 18:16.203
Oh, thanks.

18:16.237 --> 18:19.273
Congratulations to you.

18:19.307 --> 18:20.707
I...

18:20.742 --> 18:23.277
<i>well, I read this morning in the paper</i>

18:23.311 --> 18:25.545
that your book is being
turned into a movie.

18:25.580 --> 18:26.680
It is?

18:26.714 --> 18:28.548
You didn't tell us.

18:28.583 --> 18:30.484
That's because

18:30.518 --> 18:32.653
it was actually written by my competition

18:32.687 --> 18:36.423
Sarah Lazar.

18:36.457 --> 18:38.292
I...

18:38.326 --> 18:40.494
I kind of stepped on that rake.

18:40.528 --> 18:43.297
<i>- I'm so sorry.
- No no no, it's fine, no.</i>

18:47.268 --> 18:48.502
Well, come on in and sit down.

18:48.536 --> 18:50.604
Awkward family dinners are
a big tradition around here.

18:50.638 --> 18:53.106
(Bay and Toby chuckle)

18:59.347 --> 19:02.316
I'm gonna go to the
movies. You want to come?

19:02.350 --> 19:05.319
- What are you seeing?
- Whatever gets me out of the house the longest.

19:05.353 --> 19:10.157
(Laughs) This deaf studies
paper is not gonna write itself.

19:10.191 --> 19:14.027
Oh. Okay, I'm gonna go get ready.

