20:19.327 --> 20:22.963
- There you go.
- Thank you so much.

20:22.997 --> 20:26.433
Please. I remember how much my
back hurt when I was carrying Bay.

20:26.467 --> 20:29.002
Technically, Daphne.

20:30.271 --> 20:33.273
What? Just saying it wasn't my fault.

20:46.320 --> 20:51.324
<i>So I noticed your campaign
signs in the front.</i>

20:51.359 --> 20:53.226
- You're running for office?
- I am indeed.

20:53.261 --> 20:55.028
I'm hoping I can count on your vote.

20:56.230 --> 20:58.198
I'm guessing you're a republican.

20:58.232 --> 20:59.833
Why would you assume that?

20:59.867 --> 21:02.035
Rich, white, old.

21:02.070 --> 21:04.004
I'm not that old, sweetie.

21:04.038 --> 21:06.840
And besides, I have some liberal views.

21:07.909 --> 21:09.042
Like what?

21:10.278 --> 21:12.846
Like the environment.

21:12.880 --> 21:16.049
And, uh... yeah.

21:16.084 --> 21:17.784
Right, Kathryn?

21:17.819 --> 21:20.253
Oh, so now I'm allowed to have an opinion.

21:20.288 --> 21:21.888
Yeah. (Chuckles)

21:21.923 --> 21:23.990
Ooh, let's talk about religion next.

21:24.025 --> 21:26.960
So... did you guys know

21:26.994 --> 21:30.831
- that Lana's in medical school?
- Oh, wow, that's great.

21:30.865 --> 21:32.866
Yeah, this is not exactly

21:32.900 --> 21:34.935
how I imagined graduating med school.

21:34.969 --> 21:36.837
Angelo has a way of doing that.

21:36.871 --> 21:38.905
He's like a wrecking
ball with a French accent.

21:38.940 --> 21:41.074
Well, to be fair,

21:41.109 --> 21:44.010
he has offered to help
out any way that he can.

21:44.045 --> 21:46.213
If he really wanted to
help, he'd stay away.

21:46.247 --> 21:48.949
Bay, that's enough.
This is Lana's decision.

21:48.983 --> 21:50.817
I'm sure she can use the support.

21:50.852 --> 21:53.019
I'm sorry. Are you seriously defending him?

21:53.054 --> 21:54.821
He treated Angelo like a serial killer.

21:54.856 --> 21:57.924
- I wasn't even allowed to be alone with him.
- Bay, come on.

21:57.959 --> 21:59.759
You know he abandoned his first kid, right?

21:59.794 --> 22:03.029
And as soon as things get tough with
this one, he'll split on you, too.

22:03.064 --> 22:04.064
- Bay!
- Okay, that's enough.

22:04.098 --> 22:08.735
Okay, actually, it is
not gonna be an issue.

22:09.804 --> 22:12.706
I am giving the baby up for adoption.

22:12.740 --> 22:15.709
Wow, that's... great.

22:15.743 --> 22:16.910
I'm sorry. I'm confused.

22:16.944 --> 22:18.979
If you're giving the baby up for adoption,

22:19.013 --> 22:20.947
why did you want to meet us so badly?

22:24.785 --> 22:26.753
I thought that_

22:26.787 --> 22:28.989
you guys wanted to meet me.

22:37.765 --> 22:39.699
Toby.

22:39.734 --> 22:41.635
Uh...

22:41.669 --> 22:44.905
why don't I give Lana a tour of
the rest of the house before we eat?

22:48.809 --> 22:50.844
Okay, yeah.

22:50.878 --> 22:51.912
Um...

22:53.481 --> 22:54.681
(John clears throat)

22:56.517 --> 22:58.552
<i>- (Doorbell rings)
- Kathryn: Oh.</i>

22:58.586 --> 23:00.620
I'll get it.

23:00.655 --> 23:03.857
- What just happened?
- Let's just try to get through this dinner.

23:06.527 --> 23:08.695
Hey, guys, you have a guest.

23:08.729 --> 23:10.597
<i>I'm Julian Spencer,</i>

23:10.631 --> 23:12.666
Immigrations, Customs Enforcement.

23:12.700 --> 23:14.834
John: How can we help you, sir?

23:14.869 --> 23:18.572
I'm just following up on Regina
Vasquez and Angelo Sorrento.

23:18.606 --> 23:22.409
Well, they don't live here anymore.

23:22.443 --> 23:25.612
I'm aware of that. I just need to
verify that they've both moved out

23:25.646 --> 23:28.648
and that they're not
maintaining separate residences.

23:28.683 --> 23:31.384
You don't mind if I take
a look around, do you?

23:31.419 --> 23:32.819
No, not at all.

23:38.926 --> 23:41.661
- I had to say, I think she moved
- _

23:41.696 --> 23:43.997
like about two, three weeks ago, right?

23:44.031 --> 23:45.765
- Yeah, two.
- Yeah.

23:45.800 --> 23:47.667
Well, let me just take a
quick look in the guesthouse,

23:47.702 --> 23:50.637
- and I'll be out of your hair.
- No problem.

23:50.671 --> 23:54.007
Oh, I feel so rude. I
didn't offer you a drink.

23:54.041 --> 23:56.042
- Would you like some hors oeuvres?
- No, ma'am.

23:56.077 --> 23:59.946
- I gotta ask you something. Are you a Royals fan?
- (Chuckles)

23:59.981 --> 24:02.716
Can't stand them. No offense.

24:02.750 --> 24:04.918
- I grew up in St. Louis.
- A Cards fan?

24:04.952 --> 24:07.854
I'm sorry, Officer, I'm gonna
have to ask you to leave.

24:07.888 --> 24:09.589
(Men laugh)

24:11.859 --> 24:14.661
Well, if it counts, my
son's crazy about the Royals.

24:14.695 --> 24:17.697
Well, I gotta sign a ball for him
then. Come on. But you know what?

24:17.732 --> 24:20.800
- If he sells it on eBay, I get a cut.
- (Chuckles)

24:20.835 --> 24:21.935
(Whispers) Now, now.

24:21.969 --> 24:25.005
(Taps)

24:26.040 --> 24:27.774
(Sighs)

24:38.919 --> 24:41.554
(Cellphone buzzes)

24:48.863 --> 24:51.831
Kathryn, someone is blocking my car in.

24:51.866 --> 24:54.467
That would be this
gentleman from immigration.

24:54.502 --> 24:57.437
- He's here for an inspection.
- Mrs. Vasquez,

24:57.471 --> 24:58.672
I thought you moved out.

24:58.706 --> 25:00.807
That's right.

25:33.808 --> 25:36.443
I was just here visiting my
daughter. (Clears throat)

25:36.477 --> 25:39.713
Both of them, actually. You remember
the whole switched at birth thing.

25:39.747 --> 25:41.781
<i>- Pretty hard to forget.
- Kathryn: Mm-hmm.</i>

25:45.386 --> 25:47.687
Uh, don't you need to
inspect my current residence?

25:47.722 --> 25:49.689
I'm on my way over there
now, if you want to follow me.

25:49.724 --> 25:53.359
That'd be great... after I've
verified you've vacated these premises.

25:53.394 --> 25:57.363
You see, a lot of sham couples
say that they've moved in together.

25:57.398 --> 25:59.632
They put up a few photos and
toiletries in the new place.

25:59.667 --> 26:00.700
They make it look real good,

26:00.735 --> 26:03.670
but we catch them when
we visit the old place

26:03.704 --> 26:05.739
and find one of them still living there.

26:05.773 --> 26:08.575
Now, which way to the guesthouse?

26:08.609 --> 26:11.478
You know what? I better show you.

26:11.512 --> 26:13.246
Mm-hmm.

26:13.280 --> 26:14.714
Well, it looks like you're in luck.

26:14.749 --> 26:18.284
I managed to scrounge one up.
Now whom do I make this out to?

26:18.319 --> 26:20.520
Dad, Ivan is on the phone for you.

26:20.554 --> 26:22.388
Okay, tell him I'll call him right back.

26:22.423 --> 26:24.724
No, he really needs to
talk to you, like now.

26:24.759 --> 26:27.594
Okay, can you hold on to
that for me for one second?

26:27.628 --> 26:29.395
I'll be right back.

26:29.430 --> 26:30.630
Give me that. Thank you.

26:40.641 --> 26:43.476
- Yeah, yeah, I'll talk to you later.
- I'll be right back.

26:43.511 --> 26:45.445
<i>(Beeps)</i>

26:45.479 --> 26:48.214
That was Ivan. Apparently,
someone is tweeting

26:48.249 --> 26:50.183
about immigration raiding our house.

26:50.217 --> 26:52.285
How? This guy just got
here a few minutes ago.

26:52.319 --> 26:54.454
Ivan thinks this surprise
inspection was orchestrated

26:54.488 --> 26:56.222
by someone in the Sawyer campaign...

26:56.257 --> 26:59.192
apparently in retaliation for
us releasing the debate video.

26:59.226 --> 27:01.294
<i>- (Doorbell rings)
- See? These things just escalate.</i>

27:01.328 --> 27:03.329
Sweetie, can we fight
about this later, please?

27:03.364 --> 27:06.533
If immigration busts us,
your campaign is over.

27:06.567 --> 27:10.103
I am fully aware of that.
I am going to kill Angelo.

27:10.137 --> 27:12.572
- Well, now's your chance.
- I came as soon as I got Kathryn's text.

27:12.606 --> 27:15.208
- I brought Gina's wedding ring.
- Well, that's not gonna matter

27:15.242 --> 27:17.210
if that guy figures out
Regina's living here.

27:33.563 --> 27:35.062
_

27:36.953 --> 27:38.390
_

27:41.453 --> 27:42.950
_

27:47.541 --> 27:49.442
(Sighs)

27:51.445 --> 27:54.080
Hi.

27:54.114 --> 27:56.015
This man needs

27:56.050 --> 27:59.085
to look around Regina's old bedroom.

27:59.119 --> 28:02.121
I don't understand.

28:02.156 --> 28:04.991
My sign language isn't very good.

28:05.025 --> 28:07.227
Just a sec, huh?

28:07.261 --> 28:10.363
- This man needs to look
- _

28:10.397 --> 28:13.019
- at Regina's old bedroom.
- _

28:13.620 --> 28:14.596
_

28:14.597 --> 28:20.439
_

28:20.441 --> 28:23.409
Is there a problem?

28:23.444 --> 28:27.113
No no, she's just embarrassed
'cause it's kind of messy.

28:27.147 --> 28:29.082
Where's her bedroom, please?

28:31.318 --> 28:33.253
Okay, it's...

28:33.287 --> 28:35.088
it's down here.

28:43.931 --> 28:45.231
What the hell?

28:48.402 --> 28:52.171
Are you actually living here now?

28:52.206 --> 28:56.075
"No, I just like to walk around in a towel

28:56.110 --> 28:57.210
in other people's houses.

28:57.244 --> 28:59.846
What do you think?"

28:59.880 --> 29:02.215
He moved in after my mom moved out.

29:02.283 --> 29:04.817
Yep, they're friends. She lives over there.

29:09.189 --> 29:11.791
<i>Daphne: "So if you don't mind,
I'd like to go back to my shower.</i>

29:11.825 --> 29:13.793
<i>Unless you want to do my back." (Chuckles)</i>

29:13.827 --> 29:16.229
Right. No.

29:16.263 --> 29:18.865
Sorry to have bothered you.

29:22.937 --> 29:25.204
- So you're not hungry?
- No.

29:27.107 --> 29:29.108
- (Laughing)
- (Sighs)

29:32.212 --> 29:34.814
It just never ends, does it?

29:34.848 --> 29:36.182
<i>(Kathryn clears throat)</i>

29:37.985 --> 29:39.152
<i>Kathryn: Well... </i>

29:39.186 --> 29:41.721
Mr. Sorrento,

29:41.755 --> 29:43.790
what are you doing here?

29:43.824 --> 29:45.792
Oh, he's here for dinner, too.

29:45.826 --> 29:48.027
- Fashionably late like usual.
- I know.

29:48.062 --> 29:49.162
Well, I will let you get to your dinner.

29:49.196 --> 29:50.997
I've seen everything I need to see here.

29:51.031 --> 29:52.799
Sorry for any inconvenience.

29:52.833 --> 29:55.835
- No problem at all.
- Hey, guys.

29:55.869 --> 29:58.171
- What's going on?
- Hi.

30:00.207 --> 30:02.909
Hi.

30:04.878 --> 30:08.815
- Have we met?
- I don't think so.

30:08.849 --> 30:12.785
No, we have. I met you on the
elevator when I was visiting Angelo.

30:16.190 --> 30:18.057
You two know each other?

30:18.092 --> 30:21.761
(Sighs) I'm his wife.

30:21.795 --> 30:23.796
<i>Julian: Wait, wait, wait.</i>

30:23.831 --> 30:25.698
You're friends with Mr. Sorrento,

30:25.733 --> 30:27.700
but you didn't know that this is his wife?

30:28.969 --> 30:30.937
I'm sorry, who are you?

30:30.971 --> 30:32.939
I'm with Immigration Customs Enforcement.

30:32.973 --> 30:35.708
Exactly how good of friends
are you with Mr. Sorrento?

30:40.147 --> 30:43.850
We aren't really friends.

30:43.884 --> 30:45.084
Then what is the relationship?

30:46.720 --> 30:47.754
(Sighs)

30:50.858 --> 30:51.824
Umm...

30:56.697 --> 30:59.732
(Sighs) I'm carrying his baby.

31:09.743 --> 31:10.643
Sir, it's not what it looks like.

31:10.678 --> 31:11.678
There's really a very simple explanation.

31:12.712 --> 31:14.436
All this happened in Italy
before we were married.

31:14.437 --> 31:16.693
They're together. It's just complicated.

31:16.694 --> 31:18.786
This seems like a private
matter. I'm just gonna go.

31:18.787 --> 31:19.348
Okay, enough.

31:20.284 --> 31:21.689
I can explain everything.

31:26.790 --> 31:27.608
Okay.

31:28.913 --> 31:29.989
Can we talk in private?

31:32.722 --> 31:33.839
Nobody go anywhere.

31:51.280 --> 31:52.232
_

31:52.680 --> 31:54.203
_

